{{Quote|Ten thousand ''visvia'' is approximately sixteen thousand of your kilometers. Does that sound like the correct operating range?|Force Commander Mitth'raw'nuruodo|<ref name="Outbound Flight">[[Outbound Flight (novel)|''Outbound Flight'']]</ref>}}
'''''Visvia''''' were [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] units of distance, corresponding to approximately 1.6 [[Kilometer/Legends|kilometers]] each.<ref name="Outbound Flight" /> In [[27 BBY/Legends|27 BBY]],<ref name="Death">The events of [[Outbound Flight (novel)|''Outbound Flight'']] take place five [[Standard year/Legends|years]] after the [[Battle of Naboo/Legends|Battle of Naboo]], which ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' dates to [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]]. Therefore the novel must have taken place in [[27 BBY/Legends|27 BBY]].</ref> the [[Commanding officer/Legends|commander]] of the Chiss [[Picket Force Two/Legends|Picket Force Two]] [[Destruction of Special Task Force One|engaged]] a [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]] [[Special Task Force One|task force]] with a [[Chiss fighter]]. The Trade Federation's [[Droid starfighter/Legends|droid starfighters]] fought the Chiss [[Starship/Legends|ship]], however, they were close enough to Thrawn's [[Cruiser/Legends|Chiss assault cruiser]] [[Springhawk/Legends|''Springhawk'']], and were jammed after Thrawn inquired a [[Jorj Car'das|Human]] aboard [[Gender/Legends|his]] [[Cruiser/Legends|cruiser]] if ten thousand ''visvia'' was the correct operating range for the [[Droid/Legends|droids]].<ref name="Outbound Flight" />

==Behind the scenes==
''Visvia'' was first mentioned in [[Timothy Zahn]]'s [[2006]] novel [[Outbound Flight (novel)|''Outbound Flight'']].<ref name="Outbound Flight" />

